==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sagittary
<hw>Sag"it*ta"ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Sagittarius</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Myth.)</fld> <def>A
centaur; a fabulous being, half man, half horse, armed with a bow and
quiver.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The Arsenal in Venice; -- so called from having a
figure of an archer over the door.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sagittary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sagittary
<hw>Sag"it*ta*ry</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sagittarius</ets>.]</ety> <def>Pertaining to, or resembling, an
arrow.</def> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sagittate</ent>⟦br⟧
